Mesa Offshore Trust said it received itsfirst cash distribution from the Mesa Limited Partnership andexpects dividends to its unitholders to begin in July.    It said the cash distribution for March totaled 2,484,000dlrs, which will be used to repay a portion of the Trust'soutstanding 3.2 mln dlr line of credit with Texas Commerce BankNational Association. Mesa said the line of credit must berepaid before distributions to unit holders may begin.    Mesa Offshore Trust previously owed Mesa Limited Partnshipfor expenses related to exploration and development of theTrust's properties. Reuter&#3;